 to half the boom peak touched\nlast spring was reported today b f\nthe Rayon Organon, a trade public*-\nj tion.\nIts October index for deliveries wan\nthe lowest since April. 1935.\nDespite the drop, however, domes\ntic rayon yarn production in the first\nnine months established a new re\ncord for a comparable period at 181.-\n300.000 pounds, a sain of 14 per cent\nover output of 150.300.000 In the liko\nperiod last year.\nCOMMERCIAL BANKERS\nRESTRAINED ON SALES\nRonton. Nov. (AP>\u2014Ac tin* on A\ncomplaint of the Federal Securities\ncommission. Federal Judge Hugh D.\nMcLellan today temporarily restrained\nthe Commercial Banker* of Boston,\ninc.. and William E. Willard of Bos\nton from selling stock in the concern.\nA bill of complaint was filed bjr\nAllen E. Throop, general counsel, and\nJoseph P. Rooney. New England coun\nsel for the S. E. C.\nJudge McLellan ordered the con\ncern and Willard to appear In the\nL\u2019nlted States district court the 15th\nto show cause why they should not\nhe permanently enjoined from selling\nstock.\n13","height":"25935","width":"20063"}}
